291
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:17,200
Alfred, you're revolting.

292
00:16:17,234 --> 00:16:18,724
White Fairlane. Go!

293
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:22,864
It's deep. Three deep. Go!

294
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:28,276
If you ever drive my car
like that again, I'll sue you!

295
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,442
Now, you promised
to help me with my nails.

296
00:16:30,481 --> 00:16:31,607
Her silky cape...

297
00:16:31,649 --> 00:16:34,641
Oh, stop. Come on.
He's revolting, but rich.

298
00:16:34,685 --> 00:16:36,653
It's time for fireworks.

299
00:16:36,687 --> 00:16:38,621
Everybody to the beach.

300
00:16:38,656 --> 00:16:41,819
Fireworks are
for El Flamingo members only.

301
00:16:41,859 --> 00:16:44,089
Nonmembers,
please don't look up.

302
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:47,190
Just kidding.

303
00:16:58,843 --> 00:17:00,208
Breakfast is ready.

304
00:17:01,846 --> 00:17:03,279
Morning, sweetheart.

305
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:04,611
Jeffrey, you there?

306
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:06,639
Just look in the box and give me
the Stilson wrench...

307
00:17:06,684 --> 00:17:07,912
will you, please?

308
00:17:07,952 --> 00:17:09,886
Which one, do you want
the 14 or the 18?

309
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,353
The 14. I got the 18.

310
00:17:15,326 --> 00:17:16,452
Good morning.

311
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:17,620
Morning.

312
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:18,787
All right.

313
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,956
Do you have a union card?

314
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,489
I don't speak English.
I don't know anything.

315
00:17:23,534 --> 00:17:25,764
I come but I don't know...

316
00:17:25,803 --> 00:17:27,270
Hold that. That's it.
Straighten that out.

317
00:17:27,304 --> 00:17:29,465
Like that. That's good.

318
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:30,633
Who taught you how to do this?

319
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:32,107
Some bum.

320
00:17:32,143 --> 00:17:33,440
I'll give you bum.

321
00:17:33,477 --> 00:17:35,001
What are you gonna do?

322
00:17:35,045 --> 00:17:38,606
Lend Jack some money
and help him find a job.

323
00:17:38,649 --> 00:17:39,775
Arthur.

324
00:17:39,817 --> 00:17:42,285
He is my brother, Ruth.

325
00:17:42,319 --> 00:17:43,752
Jack is my brother.

326
00:17:48,659 --> 00:17:50,354
Bless us, O Lord,
for these thy gifts...

327
00:17:50,394 --> 00:17:51,793
which we are about to receive...

328
00:17:51,829 --> 00:17:54,059
through Jesus Christ Our Lord.
Amen.

329
00:17:54,098 --> 00:17:55,861
Amen.

330
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,060
Pass the buns.

331
00:17:57,101 --> 00:18:01,731
So where were you
until 2:00 in the morning?

332
00:18:01,772 --> 00:18:02,932
I was at the beach.

333
00:18:04,842 --> 00:18:08,471
Beaches are open
until 2:00 in the morning?

334
00:18:08,512 --> 00:18:10,605
The El Flamingo had a dance.

335
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:41,575
Eating singer.

336
00:18:41,612 --> 00:18:43,273
Will you guys stop?

337
00:18:43,314 --> 00:18:44,804
You've been singing and eating
since you were two.

338
00:18:44,848 --> 00:18:46,338
You sound like a subway car.

339
00:18:49,119 --> 00:18:50,984
What's the El Flamingo?
What's that?

340
00:18:51,021 --> 00:18:52,648
It's a fancy beach club.

341
00:18:52,690 --> 00:18:55,158
A lot of our
old neighbors belong.

342
00:18:55,192 --> 00:18:57,183
- Dancing and everything?
- Yeah.

343
00:18:57,228 --> 00:18:58,991
I was a good dancer.

344
00:18:59,029 --> 00:19:01,361
You're laughing.
I danced like a top.

345
00:19:01,398 --> 00:19:03,593
Don't laugh. He was terrific.

346
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:05,561
I got a job.

347
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:06,729
Yeah, with Mr. Henderson.

348
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:07,930
You must be getting excited.

349
00:19:11,242 --> 00:19:13,073
Well, I'm not going
to be working...

350
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:14,600
at Mr. Henderson's office.

351
00:19:16,914 --> 00:19:18,279
I got a job at the El Flamingo.

352
00:19:20,150 --> 00:19:21,515
Dancing?

353
00:19:21,552 --> 00:19:23,713
No, not dancing.
Parking cars in the lots.

354
00:19:27,658 --> 00:19:29,626
You're working at...

355
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:32,652
Mr. Henderson's
engineering office this summer.

356
00:19:32,696 --> 00:19:34,288
Well, I don't think so.

357
00:19:34,331 --> 00:19:37,357
I asked a favor of
Mr. Henderson to do this.

358
00:19:39,103 --> 00:19:43,233
An office boy is a good job
in his firm.

359
00:19:43,274 --> 00:19:45,299
It's the ground floor
to an engineer.

360
00:19:45,342 --> 00:19:46,468
But it's the summer, Dad...

361
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:48,705
and I don't want to be
working in an office.

362
00:19:50,714 --> 00:19:53,774
Listen, besides,
the pay is so much better here.

363
00:19:55,552 --> 00:19:56,678
How much do they pay?

364
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,846
You mean wages?

365
00:19:57,888 --> 00:19:59,947
No, box tops.
Of course wages. What else?

366
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:01,685
There's tips. I get tips.

367
00:20:01,725 --> 00:20:03,625
I don't believe in tips.
Tips I don't believe in.

368
00:20:06,463 --> 00:20:08,488
Well, I like parking cars.

369
00:20:08,532 --> 00:20:09,658
Well, you can park our car...

370
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,167
and still work
with Mr. Henderson.

371
00:20:11,201 --> 00:20:12,327
I mean, what... what is this?

372
00:20:12,369 --> 00:20:14,303
Did you know about this?
What's this? We agreed on...

373
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:17,796
Arthur, maybe you should
have a word with his boss.

374
00:20:17,841 --> 00:20:20,173
Just take a swing out
to Rockaway after work...

375
00:20:20,210 --> 00:20:22,041
Wait a minute.

376
00:20:22,079 --> 00:20:23,205
No swing outs.

377
00:20:23,247 --> 00:20:25,647
Please, no swing outs
to Rockaway.

378
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:27,446
I'll be bringing home money
every week.

379
00:20:27,484 --> 00:20:31,818
Look, there. Forty dollars.
That's just one night.

380
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:33,652
I'll be able to help pay
for my tuition.

381
00:20:33,691 --> 00:20:34,885
What about Mr. Henderson?

382
00:20:34,925 --> 00:20:36,222
Oh, come on, dad. Let's face it.

383
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:40,060
They only hired me because you
fix their plumbing.

384
00:20:40,097 --> 00:20:41,394
They don't need me.

385
00:20:41,432 --> 00:20:42,831
I did this on my own.

386
00:20:46,136 --> 00:20:47,967
I got to get ready
to go to work.

387
00:20:52,776 --> 00:20:54,505
He gave you $40.

388
00:20:57,715 --> 00:20:59,080
I'm going to practice.

389
00:21:02,252 --> 00:21:03,913
Forty dollars for parking cars.

390
00:21:06,790 --> 00:21:08,087
Eighteen years old.

391
00:21:12,930 --> 00:21:14,795
Hey, what's the matter
with your arm?

392
00:21:14,832 --> 00:21:15,958
Nothing's wrong with my arm.

393
00:21:15,999 --> 00:21:17,864
I'm just developing my left
for college ball.

394
00:21:22,606 --> 00:21:24,267
Not a bad left hand.

395
00:21:24,308 --> 00:21:25,798
Well, you know, I'm a lefty.

396
00:21:25,843 --> 00:21:26,969
Oh.

397
00:21:27,010 --> 00:21:28,637
Hey, I made some good tips
here last night.

398
00:21:28,679 --> 00:21:30,146
Is it like that all the time?

399
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:32,512
Usually, I guess.
But I just started.

400
00:21:37,788 --> 00:21:39,153
See, if I have a good summer...

401
00:21:39,189 --> 00:21:42,158
this parking lot's gonna pay
my room and board to college.

402
00:21:42,192 --> 00:21:43,523
And this ball here...

403
00:21:45,462 --> 00:21:46,952
it's gonna pay the tuition.

404
00:21:46,997 --> 00:21:48,828
I got a scholarship.

405
00:21:48,866 --> 00:21:50,163
Where are you going?

406
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,565
Notre Dame.

407
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:52,728
That's a good school.

408
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:54,499
Can't you see it?
"He's at the line."

409
00:21:55,639 --> 00:21:56,867
"The crowd hushes."

410
00:22:00,844 --> 00:22:04,211
"Fortune Smith
of the Fighting Irish."

411
00:22:08,085 --> 00:22:09,245
Wait a second.

412
00:22:11,555 --> 00:22:14,251
Jeffrey, Fortune, go see Alfred.

413
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:16,691
He always welcomes new staff
to the club.

414
00:22:16,727 --> 00:22:17,887
Better get going.

415
00:22:19,062 --> 00:22:20,893
Pretty nice guy, that Freddie.

416
00:22:20,931 --> 00:22:22,091
Swish!

417
00:22:31,008 --> 00:22:33,238
Is it necessary
for us to jump, Alfred?

418
00:22:33,277 --> 00:22:34,574
Yes, it is.

419
00:22:34,611 --> 00:22:36,203
You see, as new staff...

420
00:22:36,246 --> 00:22:38,476
you must go through
formal initiation.

421
00:22:39,483 --> 00:22:42,452
Excuse me.
Could you play with that later?

422
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:46,252
You jump off the cabana railing
and catch a wave. Simple.

423
00:22:46,290 --> 00:22:48,087
Of course,
if you miss the wave...

424
00:22:48,125 --> 00:22:50,457
you land in the sand. Splat!

425
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,724
I always like a good splat.

426
00:22:52,763 --> 00:22:56,164
This is a very old
El Flamingo tradition.

427
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,134
Let's go, pencil-necks.

428
00:22:58,168 --> 00:22:59,760
Jump.

429
00:22:59,803 --> 00:23:00,963
We better get going.

430
00:23:05,576 --> 00:23:07,635
Did you ever see
"The Defiant Ones"?

431
00:23:07,678 --> 00:23:10,238
No, and I don't think
we have time.

432
00:23:12,216 --> 00:23:14,081
Why don't you go first
and break my fall?

433
00:23:15,385 --> 00:23:17,512
Maybe next time.

434
00:23:17,554 --> 00:23:19,021
One...

435
00:23:19,056 --> 00:23:20,250
two...

436
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:21,450
three!

437
00:23:24,161 --> 00:23:25,389
Shit.

438
00:23:25,429 --> 00:23:26,589
No splat.

439
00:23:32,803 --> 00:23:34,236
- Piece of cake.
- Yeah!

440
00:23:35,806 --> 00:23:37,501
Ok. Let's go.

441
00:23:37,541 --> 00:23:38,940
Now you can play
with the whistle.

442
00:24:21,652 --> 00:24:23,085
Jeffrey, it's awfully nice
of you to carry that...

443
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,417
to the car for me.

444
00:24:24,454 --> 00:24:25,887
Any time, Mrs. Unger.

445
00:24:25,923 --> 00:24:27,322
Oh, look. There's Mr. Getzer.

446
00:24:27,357 --> 00:24:29,188
I'd like to go say hello.

447
00:24:29,226 --> 00:24:31,694
He just got divorced.
Wait for me, will you?

448
00:24:31,728 --> 00:24:32,854
All right. I'll be over here.

449
00:24:32,896 --> 00:24:34,056
Ok.

450
00:24:35,132 --> 00:24:36,258
What's new, fellas?

451
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,597
Hey, Jeffrey!

452
00:24:37,634 --> 00:24:39,397
Keep your hands off the popcorn!

453
00:24:39,436 --> 00:24:40,596
Ok.

454
00:24:42,072 --> 00:24:43,403
Who's the guy in the pink shirt?

455
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,874
That's Paul Hirsch,
number 1 cabana boy.

456
00:24:45,909 --> 00:24:47,501
Makes 2 bills weekly.

457
00:24:49,313 --> 00:24:51,372
Mr. Brody's playing
Colonel Easton.

458
00:24:51,415 --> 00:24:52,541
He owns the club.

459
00:24:52,583 --> 00:24:54,107
He's a retired
Air Force colonel.

460
00:24:54,151 --> 00:24:56,984
Brought down 5 planes.
Four of 'em were ours.

461
00:24:58,422 --> 00:24:59,946
See that fat guy over there?

462
00:24:59,990 --> 00:25:01,981
Big Sid, the watcher.
That's all he does.

463
00:25:02,025 --> 00:25:03,822
He watches these guys play gin.

464
00:25:03,860 --> 00:25:06,055
That's Charlie Cooper...

465
00:25:06,096 --> 00:25:07,757
Olympic cough champion.

466
00:25:08,732 --> 00:25:10,529
The striped shirt's
Mario Manetta.

467
00:25:10,567 --> 00:25:12,865
Swallowed a bug last summer.

468
00:25:12,903 --> 00:25:14,871
He sells used furniture.

469
00:25:14,905 --> 00:25:17,430
All summer they play
Mr. Brody's team.

470
00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:19,567
All summer they lose.

471
00:25:21,144 --> 00:25:25,376
The upside-down fan
is Phil Brody, the King.

472
00:25:27,451 --> 00:25:29,112
The guy's a genius, a master.

473
00:25:29,152 --> 00:25:30,312
Really.

474
00:25:46,203 --> 00:25:47,363
Excuse me.

475
00:25:49,406 --> 00:25:51,169
Today, Colonel.
Pull a card today, will you?

476
00:25:54,544 --> 00:25:56,034
- That's it?
- That's it.

477
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:59,011
- You throwing the 10?
- I'm throwing the 10.

478
00:25:59,049 --> 00:26:00,243
You're giving me the 10.

479
00:26:00,283 --> 00:26:01,944
I'm giving you the 10.
Take it!

480
00:26:09,126 --> 00:26:14,393
Sweet Ginger Brown.

481
00:26:15,065 --> 00:26:17,056
Shit. Thirty points.

482
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:19,864
How's he do it all the time?

483
00:26:19,903 --> 00:26:21,063
Thirty.

484
00:26:22,472 --> 00:26:25,100
Sweet Ginger Brown.

485
00:26:25,142 --> 00:26:26,541
That man is amazing.

486
00:26:26,576 --> 00:26:28,009
He's the king.

487
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:30,809
Phil Brody is the king.

488
00:26:30,847 --> 00:26:32,712
You play cards like that,
I don't have to see.

489
00:26:32,749 --> 00:26:35,684
You know, Phil,
I love a humble winner.

490
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:37,311
The up-card pile couldn't
have been more than 5.

491
00:26:37,354 --> 00:26:38,651
He got gin like that.

492
00:26:38,689 --> 00:26:40,247
I could do that.

493
00:26:40,290 --> 00:26:41,985
Get outta here, will ya?

494
00:26:42,025 --> 00:26:43,583
If I had you in the Air Force...

495
00:26:44,327 --> 00:26:45,521
What a pigeon.

496
00:26:45,562 --> 00:26:47,393
He does it to me all the time.

497
00:26:48,965 --> 00:26:50,432
Dr. Ward, a 55-year old...

498
00:26:50,467 --> 00:26:52,935
Must you play the radio so loud?

499
00:26:55,806 --> 00:26:57,296
Hey, Dad, look at this.

500
00:27:00,610 --> 00:27:02,237
Wait, wait. Let me do it right.

501
00:27:02,279 --> 00:27:03,439
- All right.
- Ok.

502
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:06,640
Look at that.

503
00:27:06,683 --> 00:27:08,344
That's an upside-down fan.

504
00:27:08,385 --> 00:27:09,852
That's very nice.

505
00:27:09,886 --> 00:27:11,012
Needs a little work.

506
00:27:11,054 --> 00:27:13,045
Why aren't you out
playing ball or something?

507
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:14,318
I don't want to play basketball.

508
00:27:16,993 --> 00:27:18,893
Come on, Bridget.
One time, for the kid.

509
00:27:21,431 --> 00:27:22,762
Hey, Jeffrey!

510
00:27:22,799 --> 00:27:23,959
Hi, Pauly.

511
00:27:25,001 --> 00:27:26,127
How are you?

512
00:27:26,169 --> 00:27:28,763
All the guys, we're working down
at the supermarket, you know?

513
00:27:28,805 --> 00:27:30,170
We're wondering what's
happening to you.

514
00:27:30,207 --> 00:27:32,869
I tell you, I got a job working
at this beach club parking cars.

515
00:27:32,909 --> 00:27:34,308
I'm making a lot of money.

516
00:27:34,344 --> 00:27:35,572
Oh, my God!

517
00:27:36,546 --> 00:27:37,877
Shel, what's the matter
with that girl?

518
00:27:37,914 --> 00:27:39,905
Nothing. She does that stuff
all the time.

519
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:42,885
Hey, Jeffrey. Meet Bridget.
Bridget, meet Jeffrey.

520
00:27:42,919 --> 00:27:44,716
- How do you do?
- Fine. How are you?

521
00:27:44,755 --> 00:27:45,881
Nice to meet you.

522
00:27:45,922 --> 00:27:47,583
Same here.

523
