00:40:17,139 --> 00:40:19,664
Jeffrey!

783
00:40:32,154 --> 00:40:33,416
Black makes you look nice.

784
00:40:33,456 --> 00:40:35,151
Put it away, OK?

785
00:40:35,191 --> 00:40:36,419
Family portrait.

786
00:40:36,459 --> 00:40:37,585
Try and look happy, dear.

787
00:40:37,627 --> 00:40:39,117
Is everyone smiling?

788
00:40:39,161 --> 00:40:41,629
I want a picture with Jeffrey.
Give us a picture with Jeffrey.

789
00:40:41,664 --> 00:40:42,858
Jeffrey, come here.
Take a picture.

790
00:40:42,899 --> 00:40:44,491
Just, come on. That's fine.

791
00:40:44,534 --> 00:40:47,094
Right in here. Come in here.
Look at this.

792
00:40:47,136 --> 00:40:49,570
I'll be in the cabana, darling.

793
00:40:49,605 --> 00:40:51,539
Nice. Yes. Just me and Jeff.

794
00:40:51,574 --> 00:40:53,701
Wait a minute!
I'll take off the glasses.

795
00:40:53,743 --> 00:40:55,040
I look better
without the glasses.

796
00:40:55,077 --> 00:40:59,036
Jeffrey! Over here, Jeffrey!

797
00:41:22,204 --> 00:41:23,330
Good evening, Mr. Brody.

798
00:41:23,372 --> 00:41:25,363
I'm just gonna straighten up
your cabana a little bit, OK?

799
00:41:25,408 --> 00:41:26,898
Sure.

800
00:41:26,943 --> 00:41:29,935
That's a nice shirt
you have, Mr. Brody.

801
00:41:29,979 --> 00:41:31,469
Thank you, Jeffrey.

802
00:41:31,514 --> 00:41:34,210
Appearance is important.

803
00:41:34,250 --> 00:41:36,275
Remember what I'm telling you.

804
00:41:36,319 --> 00:41:38,310
You are what you wear.

805
00:41:39,555 --> 00:41:40,817
You know,
I've heard that before.

806
00:41:40,856 --> 00:41:42,790
What is that,
a satin... satin shirt?

807
00:41:42,825 --> 00:41:45,157
Satin? This shirt? Satin?

808
00:41:45,194 --> 00:41:46,627
Are you kidding? Satin?

809
00:41:46,662 --> 00:41:48,687
Come here. Come here. Satin!

810
00:41:48,731 --> 00:41:50,323
Feel that. Feel that.

811
00:41:50,366 --> 00:41:52,834
Satin! Silk.

812
00:41:52,868 --> 00:41:54,460
Oh, jeez, you know,
I should have known.

813
00:41:54,503 --> 00:41:57,438
Chinese silk. You like it?

814
00:41:57,473 --> 00:41:58,940
It's great.

815
00:41:58,975 --> 00:42:00,408
I want you to have it.

816
00:42:00,443 --> 00:42:01,569
Oh, Mr. Brody,
you don't have to...

817
00:42:01,611 --> 00:42:03,442
Jeffrey, please.
I want you to have it.

818
00:42:03,479 --> 00:42:04,605
All right?

819
00:42:04,647 --> 00:42:05,944
You're going to love this shirt.

820
00:42:05,982 --> 00:42:08,780
I don't have to do it.
I don't have to do anything.

821
00:42:08,818 --> 00:42:11,048
Slide your arm up that sleeve.

822
00:42:11,087 --> 00:42:12,486
That's real nice of you,
Mr. Brody.

823
00:42:12,521 --> 00:42:13,647
Yeah, that's really nice.

824
00:42:13,689 --> 00:42:14,815
You like that feel?

825
00:42:14,857 --> 00:42:15,983
It's a nice shirt.

826
00:42:16,025 --> 00:42:17,287
- I got dozens of these shirts.
- Yeah?

827
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:19,487
Guy in Hong Kong
sends 'em to me.

828
00:42:19,528 --> 00:42:20,654
You going to school?

829
00:42:20,696 --> 00:42:22,493
- Yes, sir.
- Where are you going?

830
00:42:22,531 --> 00:42:24,556
I'm probably going
to be studying at Columbia.

831
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,227
Good for you! That's great!

832
00:42:26,268 --> 00:42:27,895
Did you go to college,
Mr. Brody.

833
00:42:27,937 --> 00:42:30,371
Yeah... Well, I mean, I didn't...

834
00:42:30,406 --> 00:42:32,670
You know, I didn't go
to college, but...

835
00:42:32,708 --> 00:42:34,107
My older brother
used all the money...

836
00:42:34,143 --> 00:42:36,008
so there was nothing left
for me.

837
00:42:36,045 --> 00:42:38,445
I went to night school.
I graduated, NYU.

838
00:42:38,481 --> 00:42:41,416
Took a lot of business courses.
Let me give you some advice.

839
00:42:41,450 --> 00:42:44,112
You can forget that
literature, religion...

840
00:42:44,153 --> 00:42:46,348
music, philosophy,
things like that.

841
00:42:46,389 --> 00:42:48,084
I mean, it's OK, but...

842
00:42:48,124 --> 00:42:51,560
what are you going to do
with philosophy?

843
00:42:51,594 --> 00:42:55,792
You've never seen a philosopher
making 50 grand a year.

844
00:42:55,831 --> 00:42:57,696
You've never seen a philosopher
driving a car like this.

845
00:42:57,733 --> 00:42:59,291
No.

846
00:42:59,335 --> 00:43:01,326
Remember what I'm telling you.

847
00:43:01,370 --> 00:43:04,066
Socrates rode around
on the back of a donkey.

848
00:43:06,475 --> 00:43:07,874
That's a good one, Mr. Brody.

849
00:43:09,345 --> 00:43:10,505
Don't do that, please.

850
00:43:10,546 --> 00:43:12,343
I'm gonna have to ask you
to get out of the car now.

851
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:14,872
Jeffrey, you like that Maserati?

852
00:43:14,917 --> 00:43:16,316
180 miles an hour.

853
00:43:16,352 --> 00:43:18,411
You step on that gas,
it's good-bye, everybody.

854
00:43:18,454 --> 00:43:19,614
Mr. Brody, he just came...

855
00:43:19,655 --> 00:43:21,213
No, no. Ron, it's all right.
It's a friend of mine.

856
00:43:21,257 --> 00:43:22,622
This is Jeffrey.
Say hello to Ron.

857
00:43:22,658 --> 00:43:23,784
Ron, it's a pleasure.

858
00:43:23,826 --> 00:43:24,952
Nice to meet you.

859
00:43:24,994 --> 00:43:26,291
Ron started working with me...

860
00:43:26,328 --> 00:43:27,818
when you were what,
21 years of age?

861
00:43:27,863 --> 00:43:29,831
- Right.
- 21 years old.

862
00:43:29,865 --> 00:43:31,059
Now he's got a big house
in Manhasset.

863
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:33,398
He's got a swimming pool.
He's got a barbecue pit.

864
00:43:33,436 --> 00:43:34,869
But he's never invited me
over for dinner.

865
00:43:34,904 --> 00:43:36,030
It's all right.

866
00:43:36,072 --> 00:43:37,198
I'm sorry.
I didn't think you would want...

867
00:43:37,239 --> 00:43:39,104
It's all right.

868
00:43:39,141 --> 00:43:41,405
Go sell a car. Go on.

869
00:43:46,148 --> 00:43:50,107
That's proof. It's never
too soon to start with a career.

870
00:43:50,152 --> 00:43:51,881
Yeah.

871
00:43:51,921 --> 00:43:53,946
Come on, let's go for a spin.

872
00:43:53,989 --> 00:43:55,388
In this?

873
00:43:55,424 --> 00:43:56,982
No. You don't drive this
on the road.

874
00:43:57,026 --> 00:43:58,584
It's got no windshield.
You get bugs in your teeth.

875
00:43:58,627 --> 00:44:00,686
Oh, yeah. Sure.

876
00:44:00,730 --> 00:44:03,494
You ever hit a bug
going 180 miles an hour?

877
00:44:03,532 --> 00:44:05,557
Believe me, it's not a thrill.

878
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,296
For you or the bug.

879
00:44:07,336 --> 00:44:09,099
All I have to do is sell
2 of these every month...

880
00:44:09,138 --> 00:44:10,435
covers my whole nut.

881
00:44:10,473 --> 00:44:12,566
- Whole nut?
- Easy.

882
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:15,270
You know, I watch guys
knocking their brains out.

883
00:44:15,311 --> 00:44:16,710
Take my brother Pat.

884
00:44:16,746 --> 00:44:18,475
Law review at Michigan.

885
00:44:18,514 --> 00:44:20,573
If he's lucky... lucky!...

886
00:44:20,616 --> 00:44:22,914
he does maybe 20 grand a year.

887
00:44:24,453 --> 00:44:27,388
That's my bar bill at the club.

888
00:44:27,423 --> 00:44:29,220
Your bar bill at the club.

889
00:44:29,258 --> 00:44:30,885
The point I'm making is...

890
00:44:30,926 --> 00:44:34,657
the salesmen of this world
make the money.

891
00:44:34,697 --> 00:44:35,959
Remember that.

892
00:44:35,998 --> 00:44:37,363
Yeah. Yeah. You're right.

893
00:44:37,399 --> 00:44:39,765
The reason I'm telling you this
is I've been watching you.

894
00:44:42,838 --> 00:44:44,601
You know what I've seen
so far spells?

895
00:44:45,841 --> 00:44:47,001
What?

896
00:44:48,344 --> 00:44:49,504
Salesman.

897
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:53,009
Salesman, huh?

898
00:44:53,048 --> 00:44:55,380
You're personable,
you're bright, you're sharp.

899
00:44:55,417 --> 00:44:57,351
Yeah?

900
00:44:57,386 --> 00:45:00,412
You're just the kind of
young man I want working for me.

901
00:45:00,456 --> 00:45:01,650
Really?

902
00:45:01,690 --> 00:45:04,784
I never kid when I'm talking
about a person's future.

903
00:45:06,128 --> 00:45:07,288
Come on, kid. Let it out.

904
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:08,591
See what this thing will do.

905
00:45:21,210 --> 00:45:22,768
Look what I found in his closet.

906
00:45:22,812 --> 00:45:24,370
It's a silk shirt.

907
00:45:27,116 --> 00:45:28,640
Looks like some kind of costume.

908
00:45:30,085 --> 00:45:32,952
He said somebody at
the club gave it to him.

909
00:45:32,988 --> 00:45:34,148
I wouldn't wear that.

910
00:45:56,645 --> 00:45:58,340
Go, Carla, go.

911
00:46:00,249 --> 00:46:01,375
There you are, Mrs. Brody.

912
00:46:01,417 --> 00:46:03,885
Straight vodka on the rocks
in a wine glass.

913
00:46:03,919 --> 00:46:05,910
Is there anything else
you'd like me to get?

914
00:46:05,955 --> 00:46:07,115
A gun.

915
00:46:08,958 --> 00:46:10,118
Go!

916
00:46:13,495 --> 00:46:15,690
Well, I'll check the snack bar
to see if they have a gun,

917
00:46:15,731 --> 00:46:18,461
but you might have to settle
for a club sandwich.

918
00:46:18,500 --> 00:46:19,990
Cute, Jeffrey, cute.

919
00:46:21,237 --> 00:46:24,138
This is my life...
being amused by a cabana boy.

920
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:27,568
Ole!

921
00:46:45,828 --> 00:46:48,592
Curt, I give you the honor
of working on the perfect body.

922
00:46:50,532 --> 00:46:52,261
And you can also work
on this damn machine.

923
00:46:52,301 --> 00:46:55,031
What is that 192? What?
No way I weigh 192.

924
00:46:55,070 --> 00:46:56,594
Are they kidding? 192.

925
00:46:56,639 --> 00:46:58,266
You look good.

926
00:46:58,307 --> 00:47:00,434
I try to...
I try to keep in shape.

927
00:47:01,710 --> 00:47:03,575
You know, Jeff, I...

928
00:47:03,612 --> 00:47:06,775
I've been watching your
gin rummy game.

929
00:47:06,815 --> 00:47:08,510
Go on. Lay down. Stretch out.

930
00:47:08,550 --> 00:47:09,710
Lay down on my stomach?

931
00:47:09,752 --> 00:47:11,049
On your stomach. That's it.

932
00:47:11,086 --> 00:47:12,246
There you go.

933
00:47:13,255 --> 00:47:14,950
Yeah.

934
00:47:14,990 --> 00:47:16,150
You know, maybe someday
you and me...

935
00:47:16,191 --> 00:47:18,489
we could sit
on the same side of the table.

936
00:47:18,527 --> 00:47:20,495
Nah, never.

937
00:47:20,529 --> 00:47:22,394
The guys you play
against are too good.

938
00:47:24,066 --> 00:47:25,590
They think they're too good.

939
00:47:25,634 --> 00:47:27,465
That's the secret.

940
00:47:27,503 --> 00:47:29,164
Jeffrey, my boy...

941
00:47:29,204 --> 00:47:31,570
God put certain people
on this Earth to give you money.

942
00:47:31,607 --> 00:47:36,237
And your responsibility in life
is to go out there and take it.

943
00:47:37,546 --> 00:47:38,706
Isn't that right, Axel?

944
00:47:40,082 --> 00:47:43,518
See, Jeff, I know a lot more
about you than you realize.

945
00:47:43,552 --> 00:47:45,349
I see a young fellow
who was probably raised...

946
00:47:45,387 --> 00:47:48,948
by a good, solid family
in Brooklyn.

947
00:47:48,991 --> 00:47:51,653
A hard-working father,
like mine.

948
00:47:51,694 --> 00:47:53,628
I loved my father.

949
00:47:53,662 --> 00:47:56,426
He sold notions
down in the garment district.

950
00:47:56,465 --> 00:48:00,026
And if he sold a lot of 1,000...

951
00:48:00,069 --> 00:48:03,300
he'd clear maybe $5.00.

952
00:48:03,339 --> 00:48:04,465
Really?

953
00:48:04,506 --> 00:48:08,943
I remember one time he was...
you know, kind of discouraged.

954
00:48:10,346 --> 00:48:12,280
And he sat there,
and he looked at me.

955
00:48:13,582 --> 00:48:15,049
Do you know what he said to me?

956
00:48:17,920 --> 00:48:20,855
"Phil, how many pounds
of potatoes will I eat...

957
00:48:20,889 --> 00:48:22,151
"before I die?"

958
00:48:28,330 --> 00:48:30,764
I don't want to see that
happen to you, Jeffrey.

959
00:48:30,799 --> 00:48:33,165
Make sure you come to see me
when you're ready, all right?

960
00:48:35,304 --> 00:48:37,169
I will.

961
00:48:37,206 --> 00:48:38,366
Come on.

962
00:48:38,407 --> 00:48:40,705
Over we go. On the front.

963
00:48:40,743 --> 00:48:43,678
Over here. Same spot.

964
00:48:43,712 --> 00:48:44,872
Get me in the front.

965
00:48:51,920 --> 00:48:53,854
Hi, Dad. Hi, Nikki.

966
00:48:53,889 --> 00:48:55,413
Look what the wind blew in.

967
00:48:58,327 --> 00:48:59,555
Hi, Ma. Anybody call?

968
00:48:59,595 --> 00:49:02,086
To what do we owe the pleasure?

969
00:49:02,131 --> 00:49:03,758
What brings you home?

970
00:49:03,799 --> 00:49:05,164
Oh, they closed the club early.

971
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:06,462
The rain killed us, so...

972
00:49:06,502 --> 00:49:09,938
Jeffrey, do you want gravy
on your potatoes?

973
00:49:13,475 --> 00:49:14,635
Dad.

974
00:49:15,878 --> 00:49:17,311
Did you have potatoes tonight?

975
00:49:17,346 --> 00:49:20,076
Oh, yes. Boiled.

976
00:49:20,115 --> 00:49:22,948
How many potatoes do you think
you'll eat before you die?

977
00:49:26,889 --> 00:49:30,347
Jeffrey, do you want potatoes
or not?

978
00:49:33,095 --> 00:49:35,222
Oh, no, thank you, Mom.
I'll just have a little dessert.

979
00:49:35,264 --> 00:49:36,959
I ate dinner already.

980
00:49:36,999 --> 00:49:39,763
I got ice cream. Come on.

981
00:49:39,802 --> 00:49:42,794
Mom, how come
you never make aspic?

982
00:49:42,838 --> 00:49:45,534
Aspic?

983
00:49:45,574 --> 00:49:47,633
You tell him when he comes back,
all right?

984
00:49:49,178 --> 00:49:51,271
Jeffrey, can I see you
a moment, please?

985
00:49:55,484 --> 00:49:56,610
Tell him now.

986
00:49:56,652 --> 00:49:59,485
I was at Columbia today,
filling out my fall courses...

987
00:49:59,521 --> 00:50:00,647
Tell him faster.

988
00:50:00,689 --> 00:50:02,554
So I talked to
a professor friend I know...

989
00:50:02,591 --> 00:50:05,458
and I got you another interview.

990
00:50:05,494 --> 00:50:06,654
For what?

991
00:50:06,695 --> 00:50:08,162
Admissions.

992
00:50:08,197 --> 00:50:09,664
Just because you're
on the list at Columbia...

993
00:50:09,698 --> 00:50:10,824
doesn't mean you should give up.

994
00:50:10,866 --> 00:50:12,800
This interview could move
you right up there.

995
00:50:12,835 --> 00:50:15,030
You still want to go
to Columbia, don't you, Jeffrey?

996
00:50:15,070 --> 00:50:17,903
I mean, you don't
want to go to Pratt.

997
00:50:17,940 --> 00:50:20,306
Thank you, Nikki, but I may not
be needing college.

998
00:50:22,544 --> 00:50:23,704
Ok?

999
00:50:28,884 --> 00:50:30,749
You may not be needing college?

1000
00:50:31,920 --> 00:50:33,854
What may you be needing?

1001
00:50:33,889 --> 00:50:35,618
Dad, let's face it.

1002
00:50:35,657 --> 00:50:37,818
The best training for life
is life.

1003
00:50:37,860 --> 00:50:39,589
I'm thinking about
going into sales.

1004
00:50:41,396 --> 00:50:43,694
The cabana boy
is going into sales.

1005
00:50:43,732 --> 00:50:45,097
Look, money's
the name of the game...

1006
00:50:45,134 --> 00:50:47,398
and if you can make it easy,
make it easy.

1007
00:50:48,537 --> 00:50:49,799
I know this guy.

1008
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:51,999
He sells only 2
sports cars a month.

1009
00:50:52,040 --> 00:50:54,270
It covers his whole nut.

1010
00:50:54,309 --> 00:50:56,072
- Jeffrey...
- See what I'm saying?

1011
00:50:56,111 --> 00:50:59,376
You don't really want
to sell cars, do you?

1012
00:50:59,414 --> 00:51:01,473
You want to go to college,
right?

1013
00:51:01,517 --> 00:51:03,451
Mom. Ma, believe me.

1014
00:51:03,485 --> 00:51:05,043
College is overrated.

1015
00:51:05,087 --> 00:51:06,645
Don't let anybody
tell you different.

1016
00:51:08,123 --> 00:51:10,717
I know this guy.
He made law review at Michigan.

1017
00:51:10,759 --> 00:51:13,023
He's lucky if he brings in
20 grand a year.

1018
00:51:13,061 --> 00:51:14,858
Now, you take this
car salesman I know...

1019
00:51:16,431 --> 00:51:19,093
that's his bar bill at the club.

1020
00:51:19,134 --> 00:51:21,102
What does
this car salesman drink?

1021
00:51:21,136 --> 00:51:22,262
Well, maybe I'm overstating it.

1022
00:51:22,304 --> 00:51:24,772
The point I'm trying to make
is it's the businessmen...

1023
00:51:24,806 --> 00:51:26,967
of this world
that make the money.

1024
00:51:27,009 --> 00:51:28,135
You know what I'm saying.

1025
00:51:28,177 --> 00:51:29,974
No, I don't.

1026
00:51:30,012 --> 00:51:31,877
Who is this person?

1027
00:51:31,914 --> 00:51:35,680
Who is this person?
Phil Brody, the King.

1028
00:51:35,717 --> 00:51:37,207
Now he knows kings.

1029
00:51:37,252 --> 00:51:38,947
What the hell
is he talking about?

1030
00:51:38,987 --> 00:51:41,114
Phil Brody owns
Brody Motors out in Rockaway.

1031
00:51:41,156 --> 00:51:43,124
He's probably the top mover
of performance cars...

1032
00:51:43,158 --> 00:51:45,524
on the whole East Coast.

1033
00:51:45,561 --> 00:51:48,257
He says what he sees in me
spells salesman.

1034
00:51:48,297 --> 00:51:50,390
What I see of you spells crap.

1035
00:51:54,303 --> 00:51:56,100
Why do you always
have to put me down?

