The kid got lucky, that's all.

1794
01:31:23,570 --> 01:31:26,038
Did we show him?
Right in the gut!

1795
01:31:26,072 --> 01:31:28,905
Mario, I stopped coughing.

1796
01:31:31,578 --> 01:31:32,738
Partner?

1797
01:31:38,685 --> 01:31:42,177
If you ever need a piece
of used furniture...

1798
01:31:44,857 --> 01:31:46,017
Enough said.

1799
01:31:46,926 --> 01:31:48,325
How much do we make
the checks out for?

1800
01:31:48,361 --> 01:31:49,521
Write them all.

1801
01:31:50,396 --> 01:31:51,556
Could I get cash?

1802
01:31:51,598 --> 01:31:52,724
Sure.

1803
01:31:52,765 --> 01:31:53,891
Let me go show him the damage.

1804
01:31:53,933 --> 01:31:57,494
Jeffrey, you're a real artist,
a genius with numbers.

1805
01:31:57,537 --> 01:31:59,334
You got a great card sense.

1806
01:31:59,372 --> 01:32:00,737
Well, it's just a game.

1807
01:32:01,874 --> 01:32:04,502
It's not just a game.
It's a way of life.

1808
01:32:04,544 --> 01:32:06,876
We came back
against a better team.

1809
01:32:12,051 --> 01:32:13,382
Not really.

1810
01:32:14,554 --> 01:32:16,818
Mr. Cooper, I have
to tell you something.

1811
01:32:17,790 --> 01:32:20,281
Gentlemen, we'll be waiting
for our cash over here.

1812
01:32:22,395 --> 01:32:24,522
So mad, Teddy's neck is red.

1813
01:32:24,564 --> 01:32:26,361
It's like this.
He's going crazy.

1814
01:32:27,033 --> 01:32:28,523
Hey, don't worry.
Your cash is coming, Jeffrey.

1815
01:32:28,568 --> 01:32:29,694
Ok. I'm going to go get changed.

1816
01:32:29,736 --> 01:32:30,862
I'll come by and pick it up.

1817
01:32:30,903 --> 01:32:32,029
Right here, all right?

1818
01:32:32,071 --> 01:32:33,129
What's the matter, Charlie?

1819
01:32:33,172 --> 01:32:34,298
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

1820
01:32:34,340 --> 01:32:35,466
Hey.

1821
01:32:35,508 --> 01:32:38,068
Oh, Jeffrey, thank you
for being our cabana boy.

1822
01:32:38,111 --> 01:32:39,544
- Ok.
- See you next summer.

1823
01:32:39,579 --> 01:32:41,672
Maybe. So long, Peter.

1824
01:32:43,349 --> 01:32:44,509
Hey, Jeffrey.

1825
01:32:46,686 --> 01:32:48,313
You played all right.

1826
01:32:48,354 --> 01:32:49,753
Yeah, I like your style.

1827
01:32:50,857 --> 01:32:52,620
Hey, what the hell.
It's a game, right?

1828
01:32:53,359 --> 01:32:54,485
Look, I'll tell you what.

1829
01:32:54,527 --> 01:32:56,995
I want you to forget
about that Yonkers thing.

1830
01:32:57,030 --> 01:32:59,430
You know, stock boy.
Come work for me.

1831
01:32:59,465 --> 01:33:00,693
With me.

1832
01:33:01,701 --> 01:33:04,829
And maybe I'll send you out
to my new place, Newport.

1833
01:33:05,705 --> 01:33:07,764
The beach. California.

1834
01:33:07,807 --> 01:33:10,503
You'd be near my niece Carla
with the pretty face.

1835
01:33:10,543 --> 01:33:11,669
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

1836
01:33:11,711 --> 01:33:12,871
I told them.

1837
01:33:13,713 --> 01:33:15,578
What are you talking about?
You told them what?

1838
01:33:16,549 --> 01:33:19,746
Well, I had to.
About you and Big Sid.

1839
01:33:19,786 --> 01:33:20,946
Your scam.

1840
01:33:23,656 --> 01:33:25,647
You can't go around screwing
your friends, Mr. Brody.

1841
01:33:29,996 --> 01:33:31,395
Phil. Hey, Phil!

1842
01:33:33,166 --> 01:33:35,066
Relax. Relax. Will you relax?

1843
01:33:35,101 --> 01:33:36,728
You'd listen to a kid
that cleans toilets?

1844
01:33:36,769 --> 01:33:37,929
You cheated?

1845
01:33:41,507 --> 01:33:42,872
Jeffrey, sit.

1846
01:33:42,909 --> 01:33:44,069
Sit.

1847
01:33:45,678 --> 01:33:47,145
At the El Flamingo...

1848
01:33:47,180 --> 01:33:49,671
the king does not
get his own car...

1849
01:33:49,716 --> 01:33:51,980
even if the car is mine.

1850
01:33:52,018 --> 01:33:54,043
Here you go, Mr. Willis.

1851
01:33:56,689 --> 01:33:59,317
Steve, thank you for
letting me use your car.

1852
01:33:59,358 --> 01:34:00,825
I'll get it back
to you tomorrow.

1853
01:34:00,860 --> 01:34:03,658
I'll be at the University
of Las Vegas if you need me.

1854
01:34:03,696 --> 01:34:06,324
Jeffrey, you are a better
card player than I am...

1855
01:34:06,365 --> 01:34:07,957
but I'm still better
at horses.

1856
01:34:09,035 --> 01:34:10,627
Steve, you're breathing
on my neck.

1857
01:34:10,670 --> 01:34:11,796
Your chariot, sir.

1858
01:34:11,838 --> 01:34:13,169
I think I'm gonna be sick.

1859
01:34:13,206 --> 01:34:14,673
Well, don't do it on my shirt.

1860
01:34:14,707 --> 01:34:16,140
It's your shirt
that's making me sick.

1861
01:34:16,876 --> 01:34:18,366
Fortune, thanks a lot.

1862
01:34:18,411 --> 01:34:19,537
It's been good working with you.

1863
01:34:19,579 --> 01:34:20,705
- Mandy!
- I mean it.

1864
01:34:20,747 --> 01:34:22,647
Mandy, get over here, quick!

1865
01:34:23,916 --> 01:34:26,180
All right, Steve.
Mandy's coming.

1866
01:34:27,220 --> 01:34:28,448
Hey, Fortune,
come here for a minute.

1867
01:34:28,488 --> 01:34:30,854
- He's breaking my neck.
- What's wrong with him?

1868
01:34:30,890 --> 01:34:32,016
This is for you.

1869
01:34:32,058 --> 01:34:33,525
Oh, he's just drunk!

1870
01:34:35,161 --> 01:34:36,321
What's this?

1871
01:34:36,362 --> 01:34:37,488
It's your tip.

1872
01:34:37,530 --> 01:34:38,690
Good luck at Notre Dame.

1873
01:34:41,100 --> 01:34:42,965
Stay away from Yonkers Raceway,
will you?

1874
01:34:46,839 --> 01:34:48,101
My tip.

1875
01:35:27,380 --> 01:35:28,540
Hi, Dad.

1876
01:35:29,215 --> 01:35:30,705
I got to get a fresh toothpick.

1877
01:35:32,451 --> 01:35:33,509
Hey, pull up a chair.

1878
01:35:33,553 --> 01:35:34,679
Jeffrey.

1879
01:35:34,720 --> 01:35:36,950
You play great accordion.
Come back later.

1880
01:35:36,989 --> 01:35:38,115
Jeffrey!

1881
01:35:38,157 --> 01:35:39,624
Hey, Jeffrey.
How you doing, kid?

1882
01:35:39,659 --> 01:35:41,058
I can't believe it!

1883
01:35:41,093 --> 01:35:42,685
Could we get another chair?

1884
01:35:42,728 --> 01:35:44,025
Good to see you.

1885
01:35:47,333 --> 01:35:48,891
He looks good, huh?

1886
01:35:49,936 --> 01:35:51,801
Should we have them bring
your food over here?

1887
01:35:51,838 --> 01:35:53,362
How's your Mr. Brophy?

1888
01:35:54,974 --> 01:35:56,168
Summer's over.

1889
01:36:00,613 --> 01:36:02,046
Summer's over?

1890
01:36:04,717 --> 01:36:06,981
I'm just standing here
watching another ship...

1891
01:36:07,019 --> 01:36:09,681
boxing its compass
and venturing out to sea.

1892
01:36:11,490 --> 01:36:14,357
It's nice to know that it
can go home if it needs to.

1893
01:36:16,028 --> 01:36:18,155
If he talks nice
to the lighthouse keeper...

1894
01:36:18,197 --> 01:36:19,357
he can always come home.

1895
01:36:20,766 --> 01:36:22,666
Yeah, well, maybe if
the lighthouse keeper...

1896
01:36:22,702 --> 01:36:24,329
didn't yell so much...

1897
01:36:24,370 --> 01:36:25,997
Well, the reason
the lighthouse keeper yells...

1898
01:36:26,038 --> 01:36:27,505
What the hell
are we talking about?

1899
01:36:27,540 --> 01:36:28,802
You coming home or what?

1900
01:36:28,841 --> 01:36:30,103
Yeah, I'm coming home,
all right?

1901
01:36:30,142 --> 01:36:31,666
But then I'm getting
my own apartment!

1902
01:36:31,711 --> 01:36:33,611
Good. All right.
Then it's over?

1903
01:36:33,646 --> 01:36:35,375
Yeah, it's over. Yeah. Fine.

1904
01:36:35,414 --> 01:36:36,676
All right. Good, good. Come on.

1905
01:36:36,716 --> 01:36:37,842
Come on, Dad.

1906
01:36:37,884 --> 01:36:39,181
This is a crowded
restaurant here.

1907
01:36:39,218 --> 01:36:41,186
I'm sorry... come on, let's go.

1908
01:36:41,220 --> 01:36:42,380
Dad.

1909
01:36:43,923 --> 01:36:45,356
Hey. All right.

1910
01:36:48,027 --> 01:36:49,187
Fine.

1911
01:36:51,564 --> 01:36:52,997
What are you looking at?

1912
01:36:53,032 --> 01:36:54,158
Eat your halibut
and mind your own business.

1913
01:36:54,200 --> 01:36:55,929
Yeah, eat your halibut...

1914
01:36:55,968 --> 01:36:58,129
and mind your own business,
will you?

1915
01:36:58,170 --> 01:36:59,364
Clementine for my brother Jack.

1916
01:36:59,405 --> 01:37:00,565
Oh, no, no!